1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,800
Codex sends a real Stop event. BeforeDone blocks completion because no evidence receipt exists.

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:16,800
The required verifier runs on the changed file and records a signed FAIL receipt.

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:36,133
The bug is repaired. A new check produces a fresh PASS, and the next Stop is allowed.

4
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:50,269
Incident Lab writes real HTML, JSON, and Replay Case artifacts, locating an exact failing event.

5
00:00:50,269 --> 00:01:00,269
The self-contained report opens in a real browser and moves from First Observable Divergence into the Timeline.

6
00:01:00,269 --> 00:01:07,300
Replay analyze repeats the evidence-only judgment without running a command.

7
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:15,208
Replay verify stays a dry run and takes its command only from the current repository policy.

8
00:01:15,208 --> 00:01:23,208
BeforeDone is open source. The product site and GitHub repository are the public entry points.
